18 SECTION 3. IC 32-25.5-3-12 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
19 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
20 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 12. (a) A homeowners association
21 may assess a fine for a member's violation of a covenant described
22 in IC 32-25.5-2-3(2) if the board first adopts a schedule of fines that
23 sets forth:
24 (1) the covenant violations that are subject to a fine;
25 (2) the amount of the fine that applies to each violation
26 identified under subdivision (1); and
27 (3) if any of the fines listed in subdivision (2) will be assessed
28 on an ongoing or recurring basis:
29 (A) for a defined period or a specified number of days; or
30 (B) until the violation is cured or another contingency
31 occurs;
32 a statement of that fact, along with a description of how the
33 fine will be calculated and assessed.
34 (b) If the board will adopt a schedule of fines under this section
35 at a meeting of the board, the board shall give notice of the meeting
36 to members in accordance with the homeowners association's
37 governing documents. The notice must include the proposed
38 schedule of fines.
39 (c) A schedule of fines adopted under this section must be
40 available to any member for inspection upon the member's request,
41 which may be submitted:
42 (1) in person;
2026 IN 1115—LS 6598/DI 101

7
1 (2) in writing; or
2 (3) by electronic mail or other electronic means.
3 (d) The board may, from time to time, amend or repeal a
4 schedule of fines adopted under this section if notice of:
5 (1) the amendment or repeal, including the amended schedule
6 of fines in the case of an amendment; and
7 (2) any meeting held to adopt the amendment or repeal;
8 is given to members in accordance with the homeowners
9 association's governing documents.
10 (e) Members may submit to the board under section 2 of this
11 chapter a written demand for a special meeting of the members of
12 the homeowners association for the purpose of voting to amend a
13 schedule of fines adopted under this section. An amended schedule
14 of fines shall be:
15 (1) adopted as proposed; or
16 (2) revised and adopted;
17 if so approved by a majority of members present at the meeting.
18 (f) After a schedule of fines has been adopted under this section,
19 the board may assess a member a fine for a violation included in
20 the schedule of fines under subsection (a)(1) if the board first
21 provides notice to the member of:
22 (1) the violation for which the fine will be assessed;
23 (2) the amount of the fine;
24 (3) the date on which the fine will be assessed; and
25 (4) if the fine will be assessed on an ongoing or recurring
26 basis:
27 (A) for a defined period or a specified number of days; or
28 (B) until the violation is cured or another contingency
29 occurs;
30 a statement of that fact, along with a description of how the
31 fine will be calculated and assessed.
32 (g) If a member is assessed a fine under this section, the amount
33 of the fine that has accrued must be available to the member upon
34 the member's request, which may be submitted:
35 (1) in person;
36 (2) in writing; or
37 (3) by electronic mail or other electronic means.
38 (h) The assessment of a fine by a homeowners association under
39 this section does not operate as a waiver of the homeowners
40 association's rights to pursue alternative remedies provided for in
41 the homeowners association's governing documents, including any
42 right to injunctive relief or to pursue a claim for damages.
