2 SECTION 14, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "exempt claim" refers
4 to any of the following claims or actions:
5 (1) A claim by the homeowners association for assessments or
6 dues and any action by the association to collect assessments or
7 dues. This subdivision does not include a claim that involves
8 the assessment or enforcement of a fine under IC 32-25.5-3-12
9 by a homeowners association for a member's violation of a
10 covenant of the homeowners association.
11 (2) An action by a party to obtain a temporary restraining order or
12 equivalent emergency equitable relief:
13 (A) to maintain the status quo and preserve the party's ability
14 to enforce the governing documents; or
15 (B) when an emergency condition exists that jeopardizes the
16 health or safety of any of the residents within the community
17 governed by the homeowners association.
18 (3) A suit to which an applicable statute of limitations would
19 expire within the notice period. This subdivision does not apply
20 if a party against which the claim is made agrees to toll the statute
21 of limitations as to the claim for the period reasonably necessary
22 to comply with this chapter.
23 (4) A dispute that is subject to mediation, arbitration, or other
24 alternate dispute resolution under applicable law, contract,
25 warranty agreement, or other instrument.
26 (5) A claim that is substantively identical to a claim:
27 (A) that was previously addressed by the parties; or
28 (B) that was resolved by a judicial determination in favor of
29 one (1) of the parties.
